article.headline: East Carolina 69, Marshall 68
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- Darrius Morrow scored 27 points, including the first four in overtime, to lead East Carolina over Marshall 69-68 on Wednesday night. The Pirates didn't attempt a shot in overtime, going 6 of 13 from the foul line. Tied at 63, Morrow made 1 of 2 free throws to give the Pirates (13-15, 4-11 Conference USA) a one-point lead with 3:20 remaining. Less than a minute later, he was sent to the line again and made 1 of 2. The third time he went to the line he hit both, putting East Carolina up 67-63 with 1:50 remaining. The Thundering Herd (17-12, 8-7) couldn't overcome the deficit, pulling within one on Shaquille Johnson's trey with 3 seconds left. Marshall turned it over 20 times, leading to 24 points by the Pirates, who snapped a five-game skid. The Thundering Herd were led by DeAndre Kane and Damier Pitts with 17 points each.
